<i>of</i> Wall-E out here.

12:44.345 --> 12:46.029
Bingo...

12:47.081 --> 12:49.866
was canceled.

12:53.571 --> 12:56.506
Hey, sexy, you want a dance?

12:56.508 --> 12:58.875
No,
I'm not a customer.

12:58.877 --> 13:00.359
My girlfriend works here.

13:00.361 --> 13:03.162
She's right over...

13:03.164 --> 13:05.632
This one time only,
I'm gonna break my rule.

13:05.634 --> 13:07.083
Let's go out tomorrow night!

13:07.085 --> 13:08.034
Sweet!

13:08.036 --> 13:09.319
Oh, shoot!

13:09.321 --> 13:12.438
I have to work tomorrow. Ugh!

13:12.440 --> 13:13.673
Hey! Brainstorm!

13:13.675 --> 13:15.592
What if we just have
our date here,

13:15.594 --> 13:19.045
maybe in
the Champagne Room?

13:21.214 --> 13:23.750
That was our spot.

13:28.810 --> 13:30.427
Hey, gorgeous,
You want a dance?

13:31.429 --> 13:32.863
Is it a jig?

13:32.865 --> 13:34.965
'Cause if so, it's up.

13:35.633 --> 13:37.200
Sorry, I only had the last verse

13:37.202 --> 13:39.703
of "Hot For Teacher" to work
on that. What was that?

13:39.705 --> 13:43.606
You laid exactly the same line
on that guy that you did on me!

13:43.608 --> 13:44.624
Sweetie, that is just something

13:44.626 --> 13:47.294
I say to these
gullible losers here.

13:47.296 --> 13:48.912
They fall for it every time.

13:48.914 --> 13:52.716
Bunch of losers!

13:52.718 --> 13:54.718
Oh, gosh, manager again.

13:54.720 --> 13:55.919
He's looking at me like,

13:55.921 --> 13:57.671
"Karma, why aren't you booking
more time

13:57.673 --> 13:58.838
in the Champagne Room?"

13:58.840 --> 14:01.174
Well, we'll show him.

14:01.176 --> 14:03.793
No! You're playing me again!

14:03.795 --> 14:06.346
And you're not even trying hard!

14:06.348 --> 14:08.148
There's no manager there;
You're pointing at a fern!

14:09.984 --> 14:11.601
Ted was right.

14:11.603 --> 14:14.454
I bet he's home right now,
laughing at how dumb I am.

14:19.911 --> 14:22.612
Did I deserve this?
Absolutely.

14:22.614 --> 14:25.615
I have told
some outrageous lies.

14:25.617 --> 14:27.968
I have told women I was famous,

14:27.970 --> 14:29.336
a war hero,

14:29.338 --> 14:31.821
that sex with me would cure
their nearsightedness.

14:31.823 --> 14:33.456
Barney?!

14:35.343 --> 14:38.762
I probably deserved everything
you did to me and more.

14:38.764 --> 14:40.430
But I have been trying,

14:40.432 --> 14:43.416
and trying hard
to be a better person.

14:44.135 --> 14:45.185
Thanks for showing me

14:45.187 --> 14:46.736
I had it right before.

14:54.228 --> 14:58.064
Look, I'm sorry we made you feel
a little suffocated,

14:58.066 --> 15:01.451
but were you really
just gonna sneak away?

15:01.453 --> 15:04.371
Well, it's just...
I really miss the city.

15:04.373 --> 15:06.706
I know you guys love it here,
and that's fine,

15:06.708 --> 15:08.024
We don't love it here!

15:08.026 --> 15:08.691
What?

15:08.693 --> 15:09.859
Come on, Robin,

15:09.861 --> 15:11.878
what kind
of life is this?

15:11.880 --> 15:13.463
Going to canasta tournaments

15:13.465 --> 15:15.165
and high school
field hockey playoffs?

15:15.167 --> 15:17.751
Oh, I think North Bellmore
can take state.

15:17.753 --> 15:19.753
With Sophie's ankle?
Doubtful.

15:19.755 --> 15:21.888
Okay, but if you two
are so unhappy,

15:21.890 --> 15:23.890
why don't you just move
back to Manhattan?

15:23.892 --> 15:26.593
Because the suburbs are
better for the baby.

15:26.595 --> 15:29.729
Who says? Who says any place
is better for the baby

15:29.731 --> 15:31.931
if you two are unhappy in it?

15:33.884 --> 15:36.386
No, no,
we live here now.

15:37.054 --> 15:38.772
And, you know,
this place

15:38.774 --> 15:40.240
wouldn't seem
so bad if...

15:40.242 --> 15:43.126
we got one of our friends
to move out here.

15:43.778 --> 15:45.561
Oh, guys...

15:45.563 --> 15:48.531
Oh...

15:48.533 --> 15:51.267
I would rather set myself
on fire.

15:52.586 --> 15:55.571
<i>The next morning,</i>
<i>Barney learned that even in</i>

15:55.573 --> 15:58.875
a city of eight million people,
<i>there's no escaping Karma.</i>

16:06.084 --> 16:07.100
Oh.

16:07.102 --> 16:08.768
Oh, hey.

16:08.770 --> 16:11.554
Sorry, can't talk;
manager's watching.

16:13.474 --> 16:14.524
Look, I am sorry

16:14.526 --> 16:16.443
if I hurt your feelings;
it's a job.

16:16.445 --> 16:17.811
Yeah, well, at my job,

16:17.813 --> 16:19.729
we don't rip out
people's hearts for money.

16:19.731 --> 16:24.317
My company briefly backed
a lab in North Korea

16:24.319 --> 16:26.403
which did, but we sold it!

16:26.405 --> 16:28.321
You know, I've worked
at that club for a year.

16:28.323 --> 16:29.706
You practically live there,

16:29.708 --> 16:31.658
and you didn't even recognize me
the night we went out.

16:31.660 --> 16:34.777
You can't pretend to be some
hurt little victim with me.

16:34.779 --> 16:35.829
I know you.

16:35.831 --> 16:37.047
Well, of course you do.

16:37.049 --> 16:38.614
I told you things
I don't tell anybody.

16:38.616 --> 16:39.799
I was honest with you.

16:39.801 --> 16:41.918
Yeah, because I believe you have
a gay black brother,

16:41.920 --> 16:43.636
a friend lonely enough
to smoke his own meat

16:43.638 --> 16:45.472
and that your mom was a groupie
for Supertramp.

16:45.474 --> 16:48.508
They named
their band for her!

16:50.845 --> 16:52.628
You remembered all that?

16:52.630 --> 16:55.014
Well, yeah.
I mean,

16:55.016 --> 16:56.299
you're more interesting
than the lyrics

16:56.301 --> 16:58.935
to "Pour Some Sugar On Me"
for the 8,000th time.

17:00.938 --> 17:02.522
You know, it's funny.

17:02.524 --> 17:05.692
Almost every woman
I've ever met was wrong

17:05.694 --> 17:07.310
to give me a chance.

17:07.311 --> 17:10.463
You're the first woman
who's wrong not to.

17:13.817 --> 17:15.117
Large black coffee...

17:15.119 --> 17:18.154
and whatever he's having.

17:18.156 --> 17:19.756
It's on me.

17:20.656 --> 17:23.009
The same.

17:23.011 --> 17:24.426
Thank you.

17:24.429 --> 17:26.846
You're welcome.

17:26.848 --> 17:29.849
1,700 more of these
and we're even.

17:29.851 --> 17:31.834
Uh, the song just ended.

17:31.836 --> 17:33.669
That mean you got
to get going?

17:33.671 --> 17:35.972
No.

17:35.974 --> 17:38.024
Do you have time
to sit with me?

17:38.026 --> 17:40.794
I don't know.
You're wearing my watch.

17:44.031 --> 17:46.733
Pottery.
Now you're making pottery.

17:46.735 --> 17:48.618
I needed a new vase...

17:48.620 --> 17:50.520
and some plates.

17:50.522 --> 17:51.788
And bowls.

17:51.790 --> 17:54.207
The china cabinet I built had
some design flaws.

17:54.209 --> 17:56.960
Why don't you just turn
this into a guest room?

17:56.962 --> 17:58.328
A guest room?

17:58.330 --> 18:00.363
You mean
a room ready and waiting

18:00.365 --> 18:01.697
for someone who isn't there?

18:01.699 --> 18:04.918
A room devoted to reminding me
that I'm still alone?

18:04.920 --> 18:08.338
Yeah, I don't need that.

18:08.340 --> 18:13.176
Ted, no matter how many things
you put in this room...

18:13.178 --> 18:15.445
I'll still be here.

