Hey.

18:27.725 --> 18:29.909
Hey!

18:30.394 --> 18:31.778
Come on in.

18:31.780 --> 18:33.746
Thanks.

18:34.849 --> 18:37.283
Oh, um, thanks for packing up
the rest of my stuff.

18:37.285 --> 18:39.619
No problem. Uh, you
want some coffee?

18:39.621 --> 18:41.955
Uh, sure. Yeah?
Yeah.

18:43.290 --> 18:44.407
So, how are things?

18:44.409 --> 18:46.376
Good! You?
Great!

18:46.378 --> 18:48.361
You know, I actually
made this mug.

18:48.363 --> 18:49.929
Oh, yeah? Oh!
Yeah. Oh!

18:49.931 --> 18:52.599
Yeah, sorry, coffee's
a little strong.

18:53.717 --> 18:56.269
How was your stay
with Marshall and Lily?

18:56.271 --> 18:58.304
Uh... a little weird.

18:58.306 --> 19:00.440
They're not loving Long Island.

19:00.442 --> 19:01.608
Oh.

19:01.610 --> 19:03.142
I think deep down, they realize

19:03.144 --> 19:05.111
it just... isn't a good fit.

19:05.113 --> 19:08.698
It's hard to admit that
sometimes.

19:08.700 --> 19:10.567
Sure is.

19:10.569 --> 19:13.870
But I guess it's better
to face it and move on

19:13.872 --> 19:18.575
than try to force something that
just isn't meant to be, right?

19:18.577 --> 19:20.293
I think so.

19:20.295 --> 19:21.644
Yeah.

19:22.379 --> 19:23.546
So, what do you think

19:23.548 --> 19:25.098
you're gonna do
with my old room?

19:25.100 --> 19:26.616
Haven't really thought about it.

19:26.618 --> 19:28.284
Oh!

19:34.275 --> 19:36.509
Who needs Manhattan?

19:36.511 --> 19:37.844
Yeah.

19:39.964 --> 19:41.964
Hmm, it's Ted.
He wants to know

19:41.966 --> 19:43.983
if we want to hang
out in the city.

19:43.985 --> 19:45.852
The next train leaves
in nine minutes.

20:03.203 --> 20:06.956
<i>Dear Lily and Marshall,</i>
<i>I don't know if you know this,</i>

20:06.958 --> 20:09.959
<i>but I never took</i>
<i>your names off the lease.</i>

20:09.961 --> 20:13.663
<i>Well, today</i>
<i>I took my name off it.</i>

20:13.665 --> 20:16.666
<i>The apartment is now yours.</i>

20:16.668 --> 20:19.502
<i>And I think I finally figured</i>
<i>out the best thing</i>

20:19.504 --> 20:21.471
<i>to do with Robin's old room.</i>

20:30.314 --> 20:33.983
<i>See, for me, this place has</i>
<i>begun to feel a little haunted.</i>

20:33.985 --> 20:36.569
<i>At first, I thought</i>
<i>it was haunted by Robin,</i>

20:36.571 --> 20:39.439
<i>but now I think</i>
<i>it was haunted by me.</i>

20:39.441 --> 20:44.494
<i>Well, no ghost is at peace</i>
<i>until it finally moves on.</i>

20:45.713 --> 20:47.714
<i>I need a change.</i>

20:47.716 --> 20:49.749
<i>And I think you do, too.</i>

20:49.751 --> 20:52.418
<i>This apartment needs</i>
<i>some new life.</i>

20:52.420 --> 20:56.756
<i>So, please, make our old home</i>
<i>your new home.</i>

20:56.758 --> 20:59.275
<i>It is now ghost-free.</i>

20:59.277 --> 21:00.893
<i>Love, Ted.</i>

